Xegony</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uarikel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arikel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 507<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/30/01 10:40:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tell me it gets better</span><hr size=1> I enjoy DAoC.  If I was just sick of EQ, I'd find something to do that I wasn't sick of.  I haven't played EQ since early summer. <p>Ahry - hero of Gaoth an Iar, Percival server <BR>
Arikel Callistrae - retired
monk of the Erollisi Marr server
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ukolobos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kolobos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 437<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/31/01 6:43:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tell me it gets better</span><hr size=1> DAoC has a lot of good ideas/features. Its new and refreshing, the graphics are great, the trade skills are good, the combat is interesting, and task/quests are interesting and rewarding. DAoC feels more immersive than EQ/AO/AC, and more like an rpg. Maybe its because i'm a big fan of rpg's, a big fan of history, and a big fan of the old tales of King Arthur, Robin Hood, Ivanhoe, etc...DAoC really appeals to me, on more levels than EQ can.<br>
<br>
I still like EQ (kinda), but DAoC really has me interested...maybe the novelty will wear of as i notice things i don't like, i'm sure there'll be some<br>
<br>
As to the &quot;kill, kill, kill&quot; type of advancement its at the heart of (almost?) all rpg's (with the exception of Call of Cthulhu which was usually be killed, be killed, be killed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). This type is the easiest and most effective method of advancement to implement in an mmorpg. You have to look for the other stuff to make the game unique and interesting, and for me DAoC seems to have done this very well. Tasks, quests, combat and trades seem really well done, and the RvR later in the game sounds like a ton of fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
I'm rambling... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
