Kalliph - 5 Scout <p><center>
<img src=http://members.tripod.co.uk/Shadowfist/whistlingkol.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/unayl7.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nayl7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/31/01 7:03:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tell me it gets better</span><hr size=1> The most important difference to me between EQ and DAoC I discovered last night.  Went hunting in Skona Ravine with a bunch of guildmates.  They were all mid 20's.  I was 6th.  My job consisted of looting and staying out of the way.  We had a great time, I gained two levels in about an hour and a half.  <br>
<br>
Point is, the game lets you play with your friends no matter the level difference.  And it will pretty quickly erase that level difference.  Which fixes one of the things I always hated about EQ, losing friends to uber guilds because they had leveled past the rest of your small guild and wanted to get into the higher level content that you could not help them get to.<br>
<br>
Yay!!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uarikel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arikel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 508<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/31/01 7:58:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tell me it gets better</span><hr size=1> Amen!  It's so cool to be able to effectively level up friends, and usually still be able to get a bit of loot and exp yourself as well.  Much cooler than having a guildie powerlevel in EQ.  I know a lot of people think that this sort of thing caters to uberguilds, but I've found quite the opposite to be true. <p>Ahry - hero of Gaoth an Iar, Percival server <BR>
Arikel Callistrae - retired
monk of the Erollisi Marr server
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ukunagi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kunagi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/31/01 8:10:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tell me it gets better</span><hr size=1> EQ: Stand, Kill PH, Sit....(30hrs later)...Stand, Kill PH, Sit.....<br>
Post on board how you have seen XXX PHs so far.  Does he really exist?<br>
Stand, Kill PH, Sit, Stand, Kill PH, Sit.................<br>
<br>
DAoC: Go find so and so out in such and such area.  Search around, find camp of evil guy.  Evil guy is there, kill him, return to quest giver.  Done.<br>
<br>
The quests in DAoC are far better than EQ.  Some people say that the DAoC quests are too easy. HA!  Not easier, just dont spend as many hours sitting on your duffer waiting for X Uber Rare critter to spawn and you can spend more time exploring the world, what a concept!<br>
